com.ibm.team.build.ant.task

Class GenerateChangeLogTask

  • java.lang.Object
    • Task
      • com.ibm.team.build.ant.task.AbstractTeamBuildTask
        • com.ibm.team.build.ant.task.GenerateChangeLogTask
  • All Implemented Interfaces:
    IStaticReset

    public class GenerateChangeLogTask
extends AbstractTeamBuildTask
    Ant task for generating a list of changes. The list of change sets and added and removed components will be created by comparing two snapshots. The change log file can then be published to the build result of your choice using the ArtifactFilePublisherTask.

    Required attributes are listed below.

    • changeLogFile - The file to which the generated change log will be written

    • One, and only one, of the following "current" attributes must be specified:
      • currentSnapshotUUID - The UUID of the snapshot to use in change log creation. This attribute is recommended over currentSnapshotName and currentBuildResultUUID because it identifies an exact snapshot. Snapshot names are less desirable because there can be multiple snapshots with the same name. Build result UUIDs are only useful if the associated build result has a snapshot contribution.
      • currentSnapshotName - the name of the snapshot to use in change log creation.
      • currentBuildResultUUID - the UUID of a build result with a snapshot contribution which will be used in change log creation. If no snapshot contribution is attached to this build result, the change log will not be created.
    • A second snapshot is also required. The "before" snapshot has three attribute options: beforeSnapshotUUID, beforeSnapshotName and beforeBuildResultUUID. Only one attribute is allowed to be specified at a time.
      • beforeSnapshotUUID - see currentSnapshotUUID for more information
      • beforeSnapshotName - see currentSnapshotName for more information
      • beforeBuildResultUUID - see currentBuildResultUUID for more information
      In addition, the "before" snapshot can be implicitly found by the task if no attribute is entered when the "current" snapshot is published to a build result as an extended contribution. The task will search for a snapshot contribution attached to the most recent build result that:
      • is not the current build result.
      • was built from the same build definition as the current build result.
      • was started before the current build result.
      • is not a personal build.
    Optional attributes are:

    • showFileChanges - If true, file level changes will be shown in the change log, false by default.
    • showVersionIdentifiers - If true, version identifiers will be shown in the change log (after the file name), false by default. showFileChanges must be set to true if this attribute is set to true
    Since:
    0.10.0.2 (RTC 5.0.2)
